<TITLE> Mobile court fines 15 vehicles in Dhaka for sound pollution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)A department of the environment mobile court fined 15 vehicles for noise pollution in the capital on Monday as part of a drive intended to bring some order to Dhaka's chaotic streets. The mobile court, operating on Airport Road, fined the vehicles TK 1,000 on the spot as well as filing cases against the owners of the vehicles, a DoE statement said. The court also seized 12 illegal hydraulic horns from vehicles plying the crucial highway as well as distributing leaflets to road users to raise awareness of noise pollution, the statement said. The drive was led by DoE director Mostafa Faruk, with magistrate Farjana Siddiqa taking charge of the legal aspects and Dhaka Metropolitan Police and Bangladesh Scouts lending their assistance. It was conducted in line with Sound Pollution Control Act 2006. b
